<https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/565000132/2025-26/evaluation> a ns1:EvaluationSystem ;
    ns1:evaluationDescription """I. Formative evaluation criteria:
The final mark will be computed as follows:
Final exam 45%. it will include the types of activities, tasks, content, functions, vocabulary, and topics covered in the syllabus.
Reading comprehension test on a given academic or professional text. 10%
Oral presentation: 15%
Skills Labs I-VI 30%.It aims to assess that the student has mastered the skills we have worked on in class: (oral)/written expression and reading/listening comprehension of academic-professional texts and associated micro-skills.
To pass the course, students must achieve a score of 50% or higher in each assessment component (1-4). Any component with with a score below 50%. Any component with a score below 50% will not be included in the calculation of the final grade.
II. Summative evaluation criteria: Convocatoria ordinaria y extraordinaria
The final mark will be computed as follows:
Final exam (45%)
Reading comprehension test on a given academic or professional text. (10%)
Oral presentation delivery (15%) on an assigned topic.
Skills Labs test (30%)
To pass the course, students must achieve a score of 50% or higher in each assessment component (1-4). Any component with with a score below 50%. Any component with a score below 50% will not be included in the calculation of the final grade.
Students choosing this type of evaluation must contact the course coordinator to receive proper instructions two months before the final exam date."""@es ;
